00:24:46,460 --> 00:24:48,570
The prosecutors will take over the case?

257
00:24:48,570 --> 00:24:49,730
Ah, that makes no sense.

258
00:24:49,730 --> 00:24:52,130
It makes less sense for you guys to be involved.

259
00:24:52,130 --> 00:24:54,890
Anyway, that's what the higher-ups have decided, so accept it.

260
00:24:54,890 --> 00:24:56,580
But Director—

261
00:24:56,580 --> 00:24:58,070
Commissioner's orders.

262
00:24:58,070 --> 00:24:59,700
Even so—

263
00:24:59,700 --> 00:25:01,740
What?

264
00:25:05,050 --> 00:25:07,260
I understand how all of you feel.

265
00:25:07,260 --> 00:25:08,990
So this is why we're giving you vacation

266
00:25:08,990 --> 00:25:12,140
and even giving you bonuses.

267
00:25:12,140 --> 00:25:13,280
Be grateful.

268
00:25:13,280 --> 00:25:15,520
What is a 'geum-il-bong?' (financial bonus)

269
00:25:15,520 --> 00:25:18,390
It's the money which you can use during your time off work.

270
00:25:19,370 --> 00:25:23,260
He remembers each of you by name.

271
00:25:26,050 --> 00:25:28,450
Sounds like a threat.

272
00:25:29,490 --> 00:25:31,530
What's with you?

273
00:25:31,530 --> 00:25:33,810
You always act like a thug, but you're so docile at times like these.

274
00:25:33,810 --> 00:25:35,800
Because I'm not an idiot like you.

275
00:25:35,800 --> 00:25:38,500
I admit that I am confused about what is going on.

276
00:25:38,500 --> 00:25:42,510
But at least I realize that that the last thing Team Leader said in the interrogation room was for us to hear.

277
00:25:42,510 --> 00:25:44,730
But you don't even know that.

278
00:25:44,730 --> 00:25:47,140
When did you start listening to Team Leader so well?

279
00:25:47,140 --> 00:25:50,800
I've never received a financial bonus before, so I don't know,

280
00:25:50,800 --> 00:25:53,770
but the amount...

281
00:25:53,770 --> 00:25:55,980
It's 10 million won. ($92,000)

282
00:26:06,380 --> 00:26:09,240
The price of silence, huh?

283
00:26:12,640 --> 00:26:14,670
Amazing.

284
00:26:14,670 --> 00:26:18,900
 Towards Morality

285
00:26:21,390 --> 00:26:23,400
Because a police officer is in prison, there are a lot of uncomfortable factors.

286
00:26:23,400 --> 00:26:27,400
Staff Captain, some people you've  arrested will be her.

287
00:26:27,450 --> 00:26:29,390
What a problem.

288
00:26:34,860 --> 00:26:37,480
I would like it if that was the only problem.

289
00:26:37,480 --> 00:26:39,160
Huh?

290
00:26:42,220 --> 00:26:46,020
It's impossible to know what surgery was performed just by looking at this.

291
00:26:46,020 --> 00:26:48,590
But seeing what vestiges I can see,

292
00:26:48,590 --> 00:26:50,850
it involves brain lesions.

293
00:26:50,850 --> 00:26:53,700
But it appears that it was successfully removed during surgery.

294
00:26:53,700 --> 00:26:55,400
Continuous progress would have to be monitored.

295
00:26:55,400 --> 00:26:58,500
Can I take a look?

296
00:27:03,410 --> 00:27:05,210
Brain lesions.

297
00:27:05,210 --> 00:27:07,800
So there was a problem in my brain?

298
00:27:07,800 --> 00:27:10,360
But it was eliminated by surgery?

299
00:27:11,520 --> 00:27:15,890
Neither I felt any pain nor is there any sign of surgery. So is that possible?

300
00:27:15,890 --> 00:27:18,750
If cutting-edge technology like 'cyberknife' was used

301
00:27:18,750 --> 00:27:21,350
an incision would not have been necessary at the surgical site.

302
00:27:21,350 --> 00:27:23,390
And it would be possible to return to daily life immediately afterward.

303
00:27:23,390 --> 00:27:26,400
Do you not feel any change?

304
00:27:32,770 --> 00:27:35,830
 The memories that used to confuse me

305
00:27:35,830 --> 00:27:38,470
 have definitely become more vivid.

306
00:27:40,780 --> 00:27:43,710
Deputy Chief, will you really let Team Leader turned over to prosecutors?

307
00:27:43,710 --> 00:27:46,880
We cannot just sit still, can we?

308
00:27:51,980 --> 00:27:54,220
Deputy Chief.

309
00:28:06,420 --> 00:28:08,290
 I was born in White Night Village.

310
00:28:08,290 --> 00:28:12,410
 And I am one of the children who was experimented on.

311
00:28:12,410 --> 00:28:16,300
 If you receive a proposition, it will be best to just accept it and not try to find out more.

312
00:28:16,300 --> 00:28:19,670
 Because you just heard something you shouldn't hear.

313
00:28:24,850 --> 00:28:27,820
There is something more, for sure.

314
00:28:39,920 --> 00:28:41,030
 I make them dream

315
00:28:41,030 --> 00:28:43,460
 without even knowing that they are dreaming.

316
00:28:43,460 --> 00:28:45,810
 They are led to believe that they can do whatever they want to,

317
00:28:45,810 --> 00:28:48,090
 because it's happening in their dream.

318
00:28:48,090 --> 00:28:50,360
 I clearly provided them with a choice.

319
00:28:50,360 --> 00:28:52,490
 Because that was real and not a dream.

320
00:28:52,490 --> 00:28:56,320
 Curiosity killed the cat.

321
00:29:07,420 --> 00:29:08,470
 Everyone is crazy.

322
00:29:08,470 --> 00:29:10,810
 They are stabbing themselves and jumping from high places.

323
00:29:10,810 --> 00:29:12,620
 They all die smiling.

324
00:29:12,620 --> 00:29:14,760
 What do I do?

325
00:29:16,180 --> 00:29:18,070
 What is going on here?

326
00:29:18,070 --> 00:29:21,230
 Because I made all of them that way.

327
00:29:29,120 --> 00:29:31,000
"Because I

328
00:29:32,060 --> 00:29:34,800
made all of them that way."

329
00:29:52,880 --> 00:29:54,570
Congratulations, Doctor.

330
00:29:54,570 --> 00:29:56,600
You finally caught the culprit.

331
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:59,830
After you told me that you were from White Night Village,

332
00:29:59,830 --> 00:30:01,350
I investigated.

333
00:30:01,350 --> 00:30:03,830
There were seven children who survived.

334
00:30:03,830 --> 00:30:06,900
But among them, none of them appeared to be me or you.

335
00:30:06,900 --> 00:30:08,120
Get straight to the point.

336
00:30:08,120 --> 00:30:10,460
Is there a reason I shouldn't?

337
00:30:10,460 --> 00:30:12,640
Right, well, yes,

338
00:30:12,640 --> 00:30:15,150
how is your head? You had headaches and you felt dizzy.

339
00:30:15,150 --> 00:30:18,890
Is it better? And what about those bad dreams?

340
00:30:23,690 --> 00:30:26,060
So it was you.

341
00:30:29,870 --> 00:30:32,250
How did you know I had lesions in my brain?

342
00:30:32,250 --> 00:30:34,910
And why did you made me undergo surgery?

343
00:30:34,910 --> 00:30:38,460
Those symptoms disappeared so it's not important.

344
00:30:42,090 --> 00:30:44,120
Let's go back to the White Night Village.

345
00:30:44,120 --> 00:30:48,060
Me and you, we were both there, at that place.

346
00:30:48,060 --> 00:30:50,670
But there is no record of us. So what happened?

347
00:30:50,700 --> 00:30:55,100
I like this about you, Doctor. You never waver.

348
00:30:58,830 --> 00:31:00,860
To be honest, that is also the scariest thing.

349
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:04,390
That I would cause people to be disturbed when they are the ones I want to least disturb.

350
00:31:04,390 --> 00:31:07,300
What are you talking about right now?

351
00:31:07,300 --> 00:31:08,600
I guess those records disappeared.

352
00:31:08,600 --> 00:31:12,600
Record keeping system from 28 years ago would not be similar to what it is today.

353
00:31:12,600 --> 00:31:17,600
So what exactly happened that day? Why did everyone die?

354
00:31:17,620 --> 00:31:20,190
The records say that everyone committed suicide.

355
00:31:20,190 --> 00:31:23,470
Although some of them appeared to have killed each other.

356
00:31:25,430 --> 00:31:27,370
By any chance,

357
00:31:29,760 --> 00:31:31,550
did I do that?

358
00:31:31,550 --> 00:31:32,960
You, Doctor?

359
00:31:33,940 --> 00:31:36,840
How could you?

360
00:31:36,840 --> 00:31:39,090
I have no idea.

361
00:31:40,210 --> 00:31:41,860
But in my dream,

362
00:31:41,860 --> 00:31:43,960
and in one of the dreams which is becoming increasingly vivid,

363
00:31:43,960 --> 00:31:45,070
in that dream,

364
00:31:46,690 --> 00:31:49,790
I caused that to happen.

365
00:31:54,240 --> 00:31:55,190
Doctor,

366
00:31:56,100 --> 00:31:58,400
Doctor, you caught the criminal.

367
00:32:00,590 --> 00:32:03,240
Game over.

368
00:32:03,240 --> 00:32:07,690
Now you should return to the U.S. That is where your family is.

369
00:32:13,130 --> 00:32:15,920
I don't feel like it's over.

370
00:32:24,030 --> 00:32:27,700
So why are there no records of the two of us?

371
00:32:27,700 --> 00:32:29,340
The memory that remains in me,

372
00:32:29,340 --> 00:32:31,530
and what is that thing you won't tell me?

373
00:32:31,530 --> 00:32:33,350
Why did you have me get surgery?

374
00:32:33,350 --> 00:32:36,190
I wanted you to live.

375
00:32:37,360 --> 00:32:40,830
You said that a monster rescued you.

376
00:32:51,130 --> 00:32:53,820
I am that monster.

377
00:32:54,620 --> 00:32:59,060
And that monster saved you again, so that's enough.

378
00:33:14,070 --> 00:33:16,460
It's easy to pulverize someone's mental state.

379
00:33:16,460 --> 00:33:18,220
I no longer have a mental state.

380
00:33:18,220 --> 00:33:19,390
I don't have a mental state.

381
00:33:19,390 --> 00:33:22,940
What is this? They even took my pastry?

382
00:33:23,000 --> 00:33:26,600
Why would they take that? Why would they?

383
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:31,050
Isn't this a suppression of the freedom of the press?

384
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:32,960
What is the broadcast station doing about this?

385
00:33:32,960 --> 00:33:35,710
This terrible situation, huh?

386
00:33:35,710 --> 00:33:37,980
Right, they're about to fire me, huh?

387
00:33:37,980 --> 00:33:40,350
What are you talking to yourself about?

388
00:33:40,350 --> 00:33:43,430
Didn't I told you to clean up this place?

389
00:33:43,430 --> 00:33:46,210
I'm about to sweep away my own life.

390
00:33:46,210 --> 00:33:49,050
But if you complain that I didn't sweep this place, I'm about to sweep you away, Hyeong.

391
00:33:49,050 --> 00:33:50,620
I can't stand to see you, either.

392
00:33:50,620 --> 00:33:52,790
Be quiet, be quiet.

393
00:33:52,790 --> 00:33:53,910
What is this?

394
00:33:53,910 --> 00:33:56,560
What is this? Omo, a monitor?

395
00:33:56,560 --> 00:33:57,710
Computer?

396
00:33:57,710 --> 00:33:59,320
Computer? What is all this, Hyeong?

397
00:33:59,320 --> 00:34:01,810
Be quiet, just set it up quickly.

398
00:34:02,980 --> 00:34:04,210
Good.

399
00:34:04,210 --> 00:34:06,620
Starting now, there is something you should work on.

400
00:34:06,620 --> 00:34:08,510
Hyeong, this is such a nice keyboard.

401
00:34:08,510 --> 00:34:12,320
Typing on it feels great. My fingers are drawn to it.

402
00:34:12,320 --> 00:34:14,220
I think I can do a good job.

403
00:34:14,220 --> 00:34:17,730
You can find out about how a survivor of White Night Village is doing, right?

404
00:34:17,730 --> 00:34:20,190
White Night Village?

405
00:34:21,330 --> 00:34:24,560
Hyeong, wasn't your phone confiscated?

406
00:34:40,370 --> 00:34:43,610
 Lieutenant Gong Hye Won

407
00:34:47,230 --> 00:34:48,970
Hate me or love me,

408
00:34:48,970 --> 00:34:51,710
when you're desperate, you think of me, don't you?

409
00:34:54,280 --> 00:34:57,250
You know about the White Night Village, don't you?

410
00:34:57,250 --> 00:34:58,480
Are you interrogating me right now?

411
00:34:58,480 --> 00:35:01,870
Isn't that something the police should know?

412
00:35:01,870 --> 00:35:04,390
Of course, you probably can't find much.

413
00:35:04,390 --> 00:35:07,660
It must have been difficult for you to even distinguish those who died from those who are missing.

414
00:35:07,660 --> 00:35:09,740
Why couldn't they be distinguished?

415
00:35:09,740 --> 00:35:12,330
It's not as if forensic technology was like today.

416
00:35:12,330 --> 00:35:14,970
How could they know the limbs that were cut off belonged to which body?

417
00:35:14,970 --> 00:35:19,200
You don't know, so you just called it 'mass suicide.'

418
00:35:19,200 --> 00:35:21,520
- A few kids did survive— 
 - I know about that.

419
00:35:21,520 --> 00:35:22,290
I know about that.

420
00:35:22,290 --> 00:35:24,770
But do you know that almost all of them died later?

421
00:35:24,770 --> 00:35:26,390
What?

422
00:35:28,060 --> 00:35:29,450
So I've told you this much.

423
00:35:29,450 --> 00:35:30,950
I treated you well without getting anything in return, right?

424
00:35:30,950 --> 00:35:32,770
So be very grateful to me, and goodbye.

425
00:35:32,770 --> 00:35:35,000
Let us cooperate.

426
00:35:36,770 --> 00:35:38,720
If you give me information about White Night Village

427
00:35:38,720 --> 00:35:40,620
I'll give you the information you want.

428
00:35:40,620 --> 00:35:41,550
Cooperate?

429
00:35:41,550 --> 00:35:43,140
Cooperate? Maybe you watched too many movies?

430
00:35:43,140 --> 00:35:45,050
Why would I cooperate with you?

431
00:35:45,050 --> 00:35:48,140
That would only be if we both want the same thing.

432
00:35:48,140 --> 00:35:50,250
Do you know why Team Leader sent you those forewarning notices?

433
00:35:50,250 --> 00:35:51,650
Is that all he sent me?

434
00:35:51,650 --> 00:35:53,150
He even sent me videos of the incident sites.

435
00:35:53,150 --> 00:35:55,730
He used you, Reporter Lee Ji Wuk.

436
00:35:55,730 --> 00:35:59,730
He used you to manipulate public opinion so that he can get close to Son Min Ho.

437
00:35:59,730 --> 00:36:01,560
 So let's hear what you want in exchange for the information.

438
00:36:01,560 --> 00:36:02,560
 Exclusive scoop.

439
00:36:02,560 --> 00:36:06,540
 I would love if everyone would just investigate and let us know the results, just like you do.

440
00:36:06,540 --> 00:36:09,430
 Maybe you thought it would be a better scoop if he just died?

441
00:36:09,430 --> 00:36:11,000
 What?

442
00:36:12,140 --> 00:36:12,950
 I'm sure that isn't true.

443
00:36:12,950 --> 00:36:16,340
 I've decided to serialize my story to clear up any misunderstandings.

444
00:36:16,340 --> 00:36:17,820
 Like those serials in the newspapers in the past.

445
00:36:17,820 --> 00:36:21,660
 You are good at diverting the attention of the people by drawing out someone's wrongdoing,

446
00:36:21,660 --> 00:36:27,360
 and instigating people by stimulating them. But I feel like there is something else that

447
00:36:27,360 --> 00:36:29,200
 you are also good at.

448
00:36:29,200 --> 00:36:31,560
So now I know. Thanks.

449
00:36:31,560 --> 00:36:33,760
Don't drop your honorifics when speaking to me.

450
00:36:34,750 --> 00:36:37,870
Prosecutors have suddenly gotten involved in this case.

451
00:36:41,120 --> 00:36:42,300
Prosecutors have gotten involved?

452
00:36:42,300 --> 00:36:44,530
Team Leader spoke about the White Night Village.

453
00:36:44,530 --> 00:36:47,220
Then the prosecutors suddenly barged in. Isn't it strange?

454
00:36:47,220 --> 00:36:48,290
Isn't it strange?

455
00:36:48,290 --> 00:36:53,060
No matter how smart you are, can you find out things faster than me even if I am at the scene?

456
00:36:53,060 --> 00:36:56,590
There is definitely something more to this case.

457
00:36:57,350 --> 00:37:03,270
Mongolians can have vision up to 13.0.

458
00:37:03,270 --> 00:37:06,470
On average, it's from 3.0 to 4.0.

459
00:37:06,470 --> 00:37:11,390
This difference can make a big difference.

460
00:37:11,390 --> 00:37:14,470
Someone who can see 10 meters ahead of them

461
00:37:14,470 --> 00:37:19,190
and someone who can see 100 meters ahead of them, what they can see will be very different.

462
00:37:23,060 --> 00:37:24,530
Go outside.

463
00:37:24,530 --> 00:37:26,550
Yes, sir.

464
00:37:40,370 --> 00:37:44,690
He believes that the Foundation will rescue him without a doubt.

465
00:37:44,690 --> 00:37:46,520
He will be loyal to his master.

466
00:37:46,520 --> 00:37:50,100
He's from White Night Village, so you should be careful.

467
00:37:50,100 --> 00:37:53,800
This. You're the one who can fix this.

468
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:58,060
Also, he'll be okay as long as he thinks it's the Foundation.

469
00:37:58,060 --> 00:37:59,720
Anyway...

470
00:38:00,540 --> 00:38:03,120
So, what are you trying to tell me?

471
00:38:03,120 --> 00:38:04,700
So he's at a higher level of development.

472
00:38:04,700 --> 00:38:06,660
How great is that difference?

473
00:38:06,660 --> 00:38:09,160
It's above being great.

474
00:38:09,160 --> 00:38:13,160
Anything that was made in the lab of White Night Village.

475
00:38:29,890 --> 00:38:33,400
 You said that a monster rescued you.

476
00:38:34,370 --> 00:38:37,360
 I am that monster.

477
00:38:37,360 --> 00:38:40,990
 And this time, too, that monster saved you, so that's good enough.

478
00:38:40,990 --> 00:38:43,560
 The monster is him?

479
00:38:43,560 --> 00:38:46,320
 And it's good enough since he saved me again this time?

480
00:38:46,320 --> 00:38:48,860
 What does he mean?

481
00:38:48,860 --> 00:38:53,800
Is he saying that the monster that saved me on that awful day is him?

482
00:39:00,240 --> 00:39:02,590
It's been a long time.

483
00:39:02,590 --> 00:39:06,000
Are you going to the convenience store? To eat ramyeon?

484
00:39:06,000 --> 00:39:07,160
I'm sorry.

485
00:39:07,160 --> 00:39:09,460
I won't go near you.

486
00:39:10,220 --> 00:39:13,340
I'm just so happy to see you.

487
00:39:20,790 --> 00:39:23,580
You were there when the fire broke, right?

488
00:39:23,580 --> 00:39:27,370
How do you know about that?

489
00:39:27,370 --> 00:39:30,400
Oh right, I was on TV.

490
00:39:30,400 --> 00:39:32,080
That isn't all that's happened.

491
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:36,000
I was abducted and returned.

492
00:39:37,950 --> 00:39:39,570
Aren't you curious about that?

493
00:39:39,570 --> 00:39:46,080
 Their body and mentality are definitely different than ordinary people.

494
00:39:46,220 --> 00:39:51,470
 The way they speak, the way they express emotions, their thought methods,

495
00:39:51,470 --> 00:39:53,450
 the way they solve problems,

496
00:39:53,450 --> 00:39:55,270
 all of that—

497
00:39:55,270 --> 00:39:58,200
I regained consciousness only after the surgery was complete.

498
00:39:58,200 --> 00:40:00,330
But there is no wound on my head at all.

499
00:40:00,330 --> 00:40:02,640
I did feel dizzy and nauseous

500
00:40:02,640 --> 00:40:05,680
but considering I just received brain surgery, I felt really great.

501
00:40:05,680 --> 00:40:07,460
I needed to know where I was

502
00:40:07,460 --> 00:40:10,170
but there wasn't even a hospital logo or name...

503
00:40:13,300 --> 00:40:18,460
Sorry, I only talked about myself so suddenly,

504
00:40:18,460 --> 00:40:20,220
didn't I?

505
00:40:21,190 --> 00:40:23,370
But it's true.

506
00:40:23,370 --> 00:40:26,470
Look at this. And here, too.

507
00:40:26,470 --> 00:40:31,000
It's possible that there could be some mark left on my head.

508
00:40:31,000 --> 00:40:32,160
Could you look at my head for me?

509
00:40:32,160 --> 00:40:34,220
Right here, it felt a little strange.

510
00:40:34,220 --> 00:40:35,700
Can you look there for me? Is there something there?

511
00:40:35,700 --> 00:40:36,920
Is there something there?

512
00:40:36,920 --> 00:40:42,590
Maybe your body was experimented on by aliens?

513
00:40:44,570 --> 00:40:47,680
Space is so enormous.

514
00:40:47,680 --> 00:40:51,630
Would there only be life on this small planet, earth?

515
00:40:52,890 --> 00:40:54,870
That could be true.

